# Special "Cold War" effect: if Manhattan Project and United Nations were built, every nation with nuclear power receives the Has Senate effect, until the Apollo Program is finished.


LATEST CHANGES:
---------------

#: Changes compared to previous civ2civ3_earth v2018_10 (available with Modpack Installer).
-: Changes compared to official civ2civ3 v3.0 (included in Freeciv release):

Fixed bugs:
# Strategic resources no longer appear on the same tile as other special resources.

Core:
- The 5th citizen in each city is the first unhappy one (was 6th).
- Added new barbarian nation that controls hostile animal units, placed randomly at the start of the game. Storms can block the movement, but can not attack.
- Enabled national trade routes again (with reduced income), that spread the effects of bonus resources. Each city can establish 1 trade route (2 after the discovery of The Corporation).
# Trade routes with foreign cities get 50% of the income, and only while the cities are allies (or on the same team).
# Enabled Tech Leakage again. Tech cost factor remains x2.

Optional (server options):
# Trading technologies in the diplomacy dialog is not allowed. Teams do not share the research pool.
- When you get a new tech by conquest, or diplomatic mission, half of its cost is subtracted from your pool of research points.
- If the pool of research points ends negative, and the negative points are greater than half the cost of the current research, then one random technology is lost, and only half of its value is restored to the research pool.

Terrains:
- Forest and Jungle can be mined to get Lumber (+1 production). Forests can no longer be transformed to Grassland directly (now Forest to Plains, and Plains to Grassland).
- Added new resources, up to 3 per terrain: Incense (+3 trade on desert), Deer (+2 food on forest, while Pheasant now +1 food and +1 trade), Marble (+1 production and +1 trade on hills), Ivory (now on jungle, with 1 less trade), Seals (same bonuses as Ivory, but on glacier), Shellfish (+1 food and +1 trade on oceans and lakes), Salt (+1 production and +1 trade on coastal ocean), Horses (+2 production on plains, while Buffalo now +1 food and +1 production), Sugar (+2 food and +2 trade on swamp).
- There are now 6 resources on Grassland, with 3 different effects: Cattle or Corn (+1 food), Wool or Cotton (+1 production), Tea or Tobacco (+2 trade).
# There are also 4 extra strategic resources that are visible on the map (and can be used) when certain tech is researched by the player (+2 production in the tile): Niter (on plains or desert, always visible, usable with Gunpowder), Rubber (on jungle, swamp or forest, with Chemistry), Aluminum (on hills or tundra, with Industrialization), Uranium (on mountains or glacier, with Atomic Theory).
- Luxury resources (Incense, Silk, Tea, Tobacco, Wine, Gems, Gold, Shellfish, Spice, Furs): +1 Luxury in cities linked by trade route.
- Food resources (Seals, Oasis, Pheasant, Deer, Cattle, Corn, Fruit, Fish, Whales, Wheat, Buffalo, Sugar, Game): +1 unit free of upkeep in cities linked by trade route.
- Production resources (Oil, Wool, Cotton, Coal, Marble, Ivory, Iron, Salt, Horse, Peat; Niter, Rubber, Aluminum, Uranium): +1 Production in cities linked by trade route.
- HP recover resources (Hospital, Wood, Coal/Peat, Oil): halved effect of buildings to recover HPs in cities without the resource required by the unit. Non wheeled Land units require a Hospital (building), wooded units require Lumber (terrain improvement).
- Strategic resources (Horse, Ivory; Iron, Niter; Rubber, Aluminum, Uranium): +1 veteran level for certain units built in the city.
- All resources reduce a bit the chances of plague, so they can be seen in the city UI. Resources traded from other cities increase the risk of plague.
# Power Plants require Coal, Peat or Oil resources available in the city. Nuclear Plant and Manhattan Project require Uranium. Apollo Program requires Aluminum.
- Deep ocean tiles require Supermarket (in addition to Harbour) to produce 1 extra Food.
- Earth scenario: Added Natural Wonders, which give +3 luxuries in the tile where they are placed, and increase a bit the risk of natural disasters. Marked with a text label, and a red flag icon. They are destroyed if the underlaying terrain is transformed.

Culture:
- Enabled culture points, produced in each city by wonders, and by scientific or religious buildings. Enabled achievements, that may give extra culture.
- The culture accumulated by each city increases its resistance against actions of enemy agents (up to +50%).
- The culture accumulated by your nation increases the cost to bribe your units or incite your cities (up to +500%). It no longer affects the chance of civil war.
- Governments no longer get immunity against bribe or incite actions. Cities with a Courthouse or a Palace are now immune to incite actions.

Gobernments:
- Halved the chances of civil war for every government.
- Appearance of Partisans in conquered cities requires the knowledge of Guerrilla Warfare by the owner.
- Added new government: Fascism (available with Tactics, that was renamed to Military Tactics, and requires Leadership and Conscription).
# Empire Size does no longer depend on the chosen government (except for Anarchy, that has no empire size limit). Every time a new government becomes available, the Empire Size increases by 2, from 8 at the beginning, up to 24 when all governments have been discovered.
# Tribal (available with Warrior Code) gets 3 units free of upkeep per city, and +1 content per city, instead of martial law. Federation gets +2 Luxury points per city.
# When Communism is used before the discovery of Communism tech (allowed by Statue of Liberty), corruption by distance increases to +1% (like Federation without The Corporation).
# Max tax rates changed to 80% for Federation and 90% for Communism, to try to even their use by the AI.

Techs:
- Explosives: allows new terrain improvements: Naval Mines that damage adjacent naval units, and Canals to join oceans separated by no more than 2 land tiles.
- Medicine: allows non wheeled ground units to recover 2 HPs per turn, even without resting. Physics allow the same for wheeled and naval units.
# Metallurgy: Galleon, Frigate and Ironclad get +1 veteran level when built at cities with both Iron and Niter resources. They are no longer affected by the Lighthouse veterancy bonus.
- Labor Union: allows cities to build engineers with one extra veteran level.
- Computers: Cities are continuously visible despite fog-of-war (once Internet wonder have been built by any player).
- Genetic Engineering: Reduces the risk of plague in all your cities by -10% (once Cure for Cancer wonder has been built by any player).
# Fusion Power: reduces -25% the pollution of Nuclear Plants, making them equivalent to Solar Plants. (Nuclear Plant production is no longer doubled).

Buildings:
- Added new building: Hospital (available with Medicine), that reduces -30% the chances of plague in the city (old effect of Medicine), and required by Barracks to fully recover damaged Land units (non wheeled).
- Mass Transit neutralizes all the pollution generated by the population (was 50%).
- Buildings with bonus to defense are visible by others (middle click on the city).
# Amphitheatre effect was reduced from 3 to 2 content citizens (upkeep cost from 4 to 2). Now, a city with all the buildings that make citizens content can neutralize up to 12 unhappy citizens, or up to 16 with the two related religious wonders.
# Research Lab doubles the effect of any Library and University in the city (+50% for each one). Library and University are no longer required to build parts of the spaceship. 
# Pollution caused by population increased by Supermarket (instead of Offshore Platforms), Super Highways, Factory and Mfg Plant.

Units:
- Increased by one the number of veterancy levels, with effects: 100%, 125%, 150%, 175% and 200%. Engineers up to 150%.
- All military infantry units can build fortresses. All worker units can build airbases, and can remove any terrain improvement.
- Nuclear weapons have to start the turn in a city with an Airport in order to move (until the discovery of Rocketry).
# Warriors obsolete by Pikemen. Chariots (like Catapults) require Lumber (terrain improvement) within the city radius (in addition to Barracks) to fully recover HPs.
# Fighter units can now cause unhappiness (when they end the turn outside national borders). Galleon, Transport and Carrier (ships with attack = 0) no longer cause unhappiness due to military activity.
# Minor adjustment to the HP recover rate of units. See the new table.

Naval:
- Trireme replaced by Galley, that can no longer navigate rivers, and become obsolete by Caravels.
- Enabled ZOC for Sea units in Deep Ocean. Cargo boats and Submarines do not impose ZOC to enemy units. Air units can be used to ignore enemy ZOCs.
- Defense bonus +50% in Deep Ocean (or Ocean with a Naval Mine) against sea units (except against submarines). Reduced a bit the cost of several naval units. Submarine defense changed to 4 (was 5), and doubled against air attacks.
- Reduced a bit some vision ranges. Most air and naval units see 2 tiles in horizontal/vertical, and 1 tile in diagonal (same as Explorers), except AEGIS cruiser and Stealth Fighter/Bomber that can see 2 tiles in diagonal too.
- AEGIS cruiser doubles its defense against air attacks (was x5), as well as Submarines.

Wonders:
- "Statue of Zeus" (+2 Shields or Coins for upkeep of units), "Mausoleum of Mausolos" (obsolete by Communism), "Copernicus' Observatory" (obsolete by Radio), "Hoover Dam" (requires Hydro Plant, double bonus to production).
# "Darwin's Voyage" (+1 Science per city, cost restored to 400), "A.Smith's Trading Co" (+1 Gold per city, +1 trade route in the city), "Shakespeare's Theatre" (+1 Luxury per city, +4 in the city, doubled in cities with Amphitheater and no Stock Exchange, cost 400), "Cure For Cancer" (+2 Luxury per Hospital for the owner, -10% chance of plague for every nation).
# "Great Library" (+1 Science per Library for the owner, obsolete by Computers), "Isaac Newton's College" (+1 Science per University for the owner, +4 in the city, doubled in large cities without Factory), "Internet" (+3 bulbs per city for technology upkeep, reveals cities for every nation).
# "King Richard's Crusade" (bonus to empire size and veteran chance, obsolete by Flight), "Marco Polo's Embassy" (free embassies, +1 trade route in the city, obsolete by The Corporation), "Eiffel Tower" (reduces pop pollution, +50% Luxury in the city, cost 400), "United Nations" (+1 move for Diplomat and Spy for the owner, free embassies for every nation).
# Continental range: the effects of "Sun Tzu's War Academy", and "Great Wall" (now obsolete by Machine Tools), is cumulative to Barracks and City Walls only in cities of the same continent where the wonder is built. "J.S. Bach's Cathedral" (+1 Content per city, +2 in the same continent).
# Global range: some minor effects that may affect every player added to "Cure For Cancer", "Internet", and "Women's Suffrage".


